    <figure class="sticky" id="solar-canvas">
    </figure>
    <article>
        <div class='step' data-width='10%' data-index='0'>
            <p>About 4.6 billion years ago, the Solar System formed and since became home to the sun, and eight planets: Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus and Neptune.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class='step' data-width='90%' data-index='1'><p>The Sun is enormous -- about 10,000 times larger than Earth in volume and weighs about 333,000 times as much as Earth.
            Earth is the third planet from the Sun and the only planet in the Universe known to harbor life.
            Please take really good care of it as its our only home.</p></div>
        <div class='step' data-width='50%' data-index='2'><p>
            Most of Earth's surface is covered with water which bestows it the charming blue, with plants adding green, and glaciers embellishing white.
            But only a tiny portion of the water is drinkable.</p></div>
        <div class='step' data-width='50%' data-index='3'>
            <p>
            You shall never feel along in this world -- about 7.6 billion humans live on this blue planet.
            Politically, the world has about 200 countries and each has its own culture.
            It is important to embrace divesity and celebrate differences. Learning from each other's merits makes the world a better place.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class='step' data-width='50%' data-index='4'><p>
            The U.S. habitats 300 million people which makes it the third largest country by population, behind China and India.
            Drag or rotate the earth to see how it compares to other countries.
        </p></div>
        <div class='step' data-width='50%' data-index='5'>
            <p>The United States is an economic superpower and has abundant natural resources.
            Its economy remains the largest in the world in terms of GDP.
                America's poor are among the world's wealthy.
                Please cherish what you have and share with those in need.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class='step' data-width='50%' data-index='6'>
            <p>Education is the key to everything that is good in our world today.
               Higher literacy levels help to enrich an individual's life as well as enhance a country's economy.
               The U.S. is among the most educated countries. But the short bars show that there are many people in developing countries cannot read.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class='step' data-width='50%' data-index='7'>
            <p>Drag or rotate to see the planets in the solar system.
            </p>
        </div>
